```

**Requirements:**
- **MUST** display all tenant installations for the app
- **MUST** show migration status for each tenant
- **MUST** display migration statistics
- **MUST** provide navigation back to apps list
- **SHOULD** load installations from Installation Service
- **MUST** handle empty installation lists gracefully

**Scenario 2: Filter tenants by identifier using typeahead**

**Description:** Users can filter tenant installations by typing tenant identifiers (base URL, installation ID, or cloud ID) with typeahead suggestions.

**Gherkin Steps:**
```
Given I am viewing tenant installations for "My Awesome App"
And there are multiple tenant installations
When I type "appfire" in the filter/search field
Then I see typeahead suggestions matching "appfire":
  | Suggestion |
  | appfire.atlassian.net |
  | appfire-installation-001 |

When I select "appfire.atlassian.net" or press Enter
Then the list is filtered to show only:
  | Tenant |
  | appfire.atlassian.net |

And other tenants are hidden
And the filter shows "appfire.atlassian.net" as active
```

**Requirements:**
- **MUST** provide search/filter input field
- **MUST** implement typeahead suggestions
- **MUST** filter by tenant identifier (base URL, installation ID, cloud ID)
- **MUST** update list in real-time as user types
- **SHOULD** highlight matching text in suggestions
- **MUST** handle no matches gracefully

**Scenario 3: Clear filter and view all tenants**

**Description:** Users can clear applied filters to view all tenant installations and see overall migration statistics.

**Gherkin Steps:**
```
Given I have applied a filter showing only "appfire.atlassian.net"
When I click the "Clear" or "X" button on the filter
Then the filter is cleared
And all tenant installations are displayed again
And migration statistics reflect all tenants
```

**Requirements:**
- **MUST** provide clear filter functionality
- **MUST** restore full list when filter is cleared
- **MUST** update statistics to reflect all tenants
- **SHOULD** reset filter input field

**Scenario 4: Enable migration for a single tenant**

**Description:** App owners can enable migration for individual tenants by clicking the Enable button, which sets the migration status to IN_PROGRESS.

**Gherkin Steps:**
```
Given I am viewing tenant installations for "My Awesome App"
And there is a tenant "appfire.atlassian.net" with status NOT_STARTED
When I click the "Enable" button for "appfire.atlassian.net"
Then I see a confirmation dialog: "Enable migration for appfire.atlassian.net?"

When I confirm the action
Then the migration is enabled
And the status changes to IN_PROGRESS
And I see a success message: "Migration enabled for appfire.atlassian.net"
And the Enable button is replaced with "Details" button
And the migration process begins
```

**Requirements:**
- **MUST** provide Enable button for NOT_STARTED tenants
- **MUST** show confirmation dialog before enabling
- **MUST** update status to IN_PROGRESS after confirmation
- **MUST** trigger migration process
- **MUST** update UI to reflect new status
- **SHOULD** show loading state during enable operation

**Scenario 5: Rollback migration for a single tenant**

**Description:** App owners can rollback failed migrations, but rollback is disabled for migrations in progress. The system shows appropriate button states and confirmation dialogs.

**Gherkin Steps:**
```
Given I am viewing tenant installations for "My Awesome App"
And there is a tenant "enterprise.atlassian.net" with status FAILED
When I view the actions for "enterprise.atlassian.net"
Then I see a "Rollback" button enabled

When I click the "Rollback" button
Then I see a confirmation dialog: "Rollback migration for enterprise.atlassian.net? This will revert the migration."

When I confirm the rollback
Then the rollback process begins
And I see a success message: "Rollback initiated for enterprise.atlassian.net"
And the status changes appropriately

Given there is a tenant "startup.atlassian.net" with status IN_PROGRESS
When I view the actions for "startup.atlassian.net"
Then the "Rollback" button is disabled
And I see a tooltip: "Rollback is only available for failed migrations"
```

**Requirements:**
- **MUST** enable Rollback button only for FAILED migrations
- **MUST** disable Rollback button for IN_PROGRESS migrations
- **MUST** show confirmation dialog before rollback
- **MUST** trigger rollback process after confirmation
- **MUST** update status after rollback
- **SHOULD** show tooltip explaining why rollback is disabled

**Scenario 6: Open bulk migration modal dialog**

**Description:** Users can open a modal dialog to perform bulk migration operations on multiple tenants simultaneously.

**Gherkin Steps:**
