Given I am viewing tenant installations for "My Awesome App"
And there are multiple tenants with status NOT_STARTED
When I click the "Bulk Operations" button
Then a modal dialog opens
And I see:
  | Element | Description |
  | Checkboxes | Select multiple tenants |
  | Select All | Select/deselect all tenants |
  | Action Dropdown | Choose action (Enable, Rollback) |
  | Selected Count | Number of selected tenants |
  | Apply Button | Execute bulk action |
  | Cancel Button | Close modal without action |

When I select multiple tenants
Then the selected count updates
And I can choose a bulk action
```

**Requirements:**
- **MUST** provide bulk operations functionality
- **MUST** allow selecting multiple tenants
- **MUST** show selected count
- **MUST** provide action dropdown with available operations
- **MUST** validate selected tenants are eligible for chosen action
- **SHOULD** show confirmation before applying bulk action

### Rule 5: Migration Details Display Feature

**Feature Description:**
Enables app owners to view detailed migration information for tenant installations, including BPS job status, progress tracking, error handling, and status refresh capabilities. Provides comprehensive insights into individual migration processes.

**Feature: Migration Details Display for Tenant Installations**
```
As an app owner or administrator
I want to view detailed migration information for tenant installations
So that I can monitor migration progress, troubleshoot issues, and track completion status
```

**Background:**
```
Given I am viewing the tenant installations for app "My Awesome App"
  And the app has the following tenant installations:
    | Tenant | Installation ID | Cloud ID | Current Status |
    | appfire.atlassian.net | "ari:cloud:ecosystem::installation/inst-001" | "ari:cloud:ecosystem::site/cloud-001" | IN_PROGRESS |
    | startup.atlassian.net | "ari:cloud:ecosystem::installation/inst-002" | "ari:cloud:ecosystem::site/cloud-002" | COMPLETED |
    | company.atlassian.net | "ari:cloud:ecosystem::installation/inst-003" | "ari:cloud:ecosystem::site/cloud-003" | FAILED |
    | enterprise.atlassian.net | "ari:cloud:ecosystem::installation/inst-004" | "ari:cloud:ecosystem::site/cloud-004" | COMPLETED |
    | newtenant.atlassian.net | "ari:cloud:ecosystem::installation/inst-005" | "ari:cloud:ecosystem::site/cloud-005" | NOT_STARTED |
  And the BPS (Business Process Service) provides migration job status via REST API
  And the migration job status API endpoint is "/bps-api/jobs/status/{jobId}/{customerId}"
```

**Scenario 1: View migration details for in-progress tenant**

**Description:** Users can view detailed migration information for tenants with IN_PROGRESS status, including BPS job status, progress tracking, and refresh capabilities.

**Gherkin Steps:**
```
Given I am viewing tenant installations for "My Awesome App"
And there is a tenant "appfire.atlassian.net" with status IN_PROGRESS
When I click the "Details" button for "appfire.atlassian.net"
