### Rule 18: High Level Architecture

**Architecture Components:**

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    Migration Service Backoffice            │
│              (Manual Trigger, Tracking, Reporting)          │
└──────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┘
                       │
                       ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              Batch Processing Service (BPS)                  │
│         (Orchestration, Execution, Job Management)            │
└──────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┘
                       │
                       ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                   Migration Stack                            │
│              (Producer: Extract & Transform)                 │
│              (Consumer: Load to Forge Storage)              │
└──────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┘
                       │
                       ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              Forge App (Migration Ready)                     │
│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │
│  │  Web Trigger: Migration Data Ingestion              │   │
│  │  Data Access Layer: Route by Migration Status Flag  │   │
│  │  Forge Storage: KVS/SQL                             │   │
│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

**Data Flow:**
1. Migration triggered via Backoffice
2. BPS orchestrates migration process
3. Migration Stack Producer extracts data from external source
4. Migration Stack Consumer loads data via Web Trigger
5. Forge App ingests data into Forge Storage
6. Migration status tracked and reported via Backoffice

**Requirements:**
